description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nurse Consultant - Rheumatology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 8B&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent, Full Time - 37.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**Applications without Rheumatology experience will also be considered**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will lead on the the development of the strategic direction for nursing practice within Rheumatology, working in partnership with medical and nursing leaders to develop the service to meet the present and future patient needs .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The postholder will be the nursing lead for the Centre of Excellence for Behçet’s Syndrome, which is one of only 3 centres nationally, and will work in partnership with the Director and other key colleagues including the other centres and NHSE/I to promote and develop the work of the Centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be a clinical expert and take a clinical leadership role in providing the highest level of quality, expert practice for Rheumatology nursing. This involves championing and pioneering innovative practice, delivering high quality person centered care. Acting as a catalyst for change in practice and service development, the postholder will be able to apply challenge to professional and organisational boundaries and generate new solutions that best meet the needs of people using the Rheumatology service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work both collaboratively and autonomously, using advanced knowledge and skills to shape and develop services within Rheumatology , ensuring that the nursing workforce and skills are developed and equipped to provide the care required now and in the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Cristina Estrach, Clinical Director for Rheumatology&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: cristina.estrach@liverpoolft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 0151 529 3342&lt;/p&gt;
